And it was all-- there was
this wanting and creating

00:40:37.440 --> 00:40:40.050 align:middle line:84%
of attachment and wanting
and wanting more stuff.

00:40:40.050 --> 00:40:42.360 align:middle line:84%
So I sort of got swept
into that in a way.

00:40:42.360 --> 00:40:49.410 align:middle line:90%


00:40:49.410 --> 00:40:50.670 align:middle line:90%
So yeah, I studied business.

00:40:50.670 --> 00:40:53.700 align:middle line:84%
And I was involved in finance
and more specifically,

00:40:53.700 --> 00:40:54.880 align:middle line:90%
the stock market.

00:40:54.880 --> 00:40:58.450 align:middle line:84%
So we used to help people
manage their money.

00:40:58.450 --> 00:41:01.590 align:middle line:84%
And one of the
organizations I worked with,

00:41:01.590 --> 00:41:05.280 align:middle line:84%
we used to manage hundreds of
millions of dollars for people.

00:41:05.280 --> 00:41:09.140 align:middle line:84%
I wasn't from that background,
from a conservative sort

00:41:09.140 --> 00:41:09.940 align:middle line:90%
of upbringing.

00:41:09.940 --> 00:41:12.270 align:middle line:84%
Then all of a
sudden, I'm involved

00:41:12.270 --> 00:41:15.300 align:middle line:84%
with guys that are
driving luxury cars

00:41:15.300 --> 00:41:19.130 align:middle line:84%
and living in expensive
houses in Sydney's suburbs.

00:41:19.130 --> 00:41:22.430 align:middle line:90%
It's sort of a bit overwhelming.

00:41:22.430 --> 00:41:24.380 align:middle line:84%
A lot of the guys
that I'd work with,

00:41:24.380 --> 00:41:27.710 align:middle line:90%
they were multimillionaires.

00:41:27.710 --> 00:41:29.990 align:middle line:90%
But $20 million wasn't enough.

00:41:29.990 --> 00:41:33.080 align:middle line:84%
So they have to
have the three cars.

00:41:33.080 --> 00:41:34.790 align:middle line:84%
They have to have
a holiday home.

00:41:34.790 --> 00:41:37.400 align:middle line:90%
They have to have a boat.

00:41:37.400 --> 00:41:40.350 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is you can
get trapped in that lifestyle.

00:41:40.350 --> 00:41:47.550 align:middle line:90%


00:41:47.550 --> 00:41:54.420 align:middle line:84%
So the idea is to have native
plants mixed among fruit trees.

00:41:54.420 --> 00:41:55.710 align:middle line:90%
So we've got natives here.

00:41:55.710 --> 00:41:58.430 align:middle line:90%
We've got a tamarillo here.

00:41:58.430 --> 00:42:02.220 align:middle line:84%
We've got manuka and kanuka
and [INAUDIBLE] natives.

00:42:02.220 --> 00:42:04.620 align:middle line:90%
We've got a cabbage tree here.

00:42:04.620 --> 00:42:06.820 align:middle line:90%
This is a pine nut.

00:42:06.820 --> 00:42:10.675 align:middle line:84%
So those are real expensive
nuts you get in a supermarket.

00:42:10.675 --> 00:42:11.550 align:middle line:90%
This is one of those.

00:42:11.550 --> 00:42:15.550 align:middle line:84%
It takes about 10 years to get
any fruit on it or any nuts,

00:42:15.550 --> 00:42:17.310 align:middle line:90%
so that's a long-term project.

00:42:17.310 --> 00:42:20.520 align:middle line:84%
And then over here
we've got a fig tree,

00:42:20.520 --> 00:42:23.520 align:middle line:90%
which is fruiting quite nicely.

00:42:23.520 --> 00:42:26.370 align:middle line:84%
And then-- oh, for the
monarch butterflies,

00:42:26.370 --> 00:42:29.215 align:middle line:84%
we've got a couple of swan
plants, which they really

00:42:29.215 --> 00:42:30.015 align:middle line:90%
enjoy.

00:42:30.015 --> 00:42:33.650 align:middle line:84%
And we might be
lucky to see one.

00:42:33.650 --> 00:42:35.720 align:middle line:90%
Here he comes now.

00:42:35.720 --> 00:42:39.810 align:middle line:84%
It was only after Beth, my
wife, and I made the move

00:42:39.810 --> 00:42:41.580 align:middle line:84%
to New Zealand--
we just had enough

00:42:41.580 --> 00:42:46.440 align:middle line:84%
of the whole corporate life,
and we wanted a slower, simpler

00:42:46.440 --> 00:42:47.430 align:middle line:90%
lifestyle.

00:42:47.430 --> 00:42:50.550 align:middle line:84%
It was then the realization
sort of hit home.

00:42:50.550 --> 00:42:55.040 align:middle line:84%
I started to research more,
read hundreds of articles

00:42:55.040 --> 00:42:57.000 align:middle line:84%
and watched hundreds
of documentaries

00:42:57.000 --> 00:42:58.170 align:middle line:90%
and all sorts of stuff.

00:42:58.170 --> 00:43:00.910 align:middle line:84%
Then I started to
really understand, wow,

00:43:00.910 --> 00:43:03.330 align:middle line:84%
we've got some
serious issues here,

00:43:03.330 --> 00:43:05.440 align:middle line:84%
and no one's really
talking about this stuff.

00:43:05.440 --> 00:43:07.650 align:middle line:90%
And it's quite scary.

00:43:07.650 --> 00:43:11.380 align:middle line:90%


00:43:11.380 --> 00:43:15.790 align:middle line:84%
I guess with realization
of some of the broader

00:43:15.790 --> 00:43:20.050 align:middle line:84%
issues such as climate
change, peak oil or resource

00:43:20.050 --> 00:43:23.020 align:middle line:84%
depletion, and the
extinction crisis

00:43:23.020 --> 00:43:24.850 align:middle line:84%
we're currently going
through-- and it's

00:43:24.850 --> 00:43:28.060 align:middle line:84%
sort of like these
massive issues are

00:43:28.060 --> 00:43:33.400 align:middle line:84%
being given lip service by
governments and organizations.

00:43:33.400 --> 00:43:35.830 align:middle line:84%
It's like, oh, it'll
just won't happen.

00:43:35.830 --> 00:43:38.117 align:middle line:84%
Or the system will
solve this problem.

00:43:38.117 --> 00:43:39.700 align:middle line:84%
And that's what it
sort of feels like.

00:43:39.700 --> 00:43:42.400 align:middle line:90%


00:43:42.400 --> 00:43:44.710 align:middle line:84%
So I guess that brings
up a lot of emotions,

00:43:44.710 --> 00:43:48.160 align:middle line:84%
like frustration
and anger and guilt.

00:43:48.160 --> 00:43:51.350 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, why isn't someone
doing something about this?

00:43:51.350 --> 00:43:52.150 align:middle line:90%
Here we go.

00:43:52.150 --> 00:43:52.820 align:middle line:90%
Here's a strawberry.

00:43:52.820 --> 00:43:53.653 align:middle line:90%
Here's a strawberry.

00:43:53.653 --> 00:43:55.070 align:middle line:90%
So this is a nice one.

00:43:55.070 --> 00:43:57.760 align:middle line:90%
Look at the color on it thing.

00:43:57.760 --> 00:43:59.560 align:middle line:84%
Then I started to
research permaculture

00:43:59.560 --> 00:44:03.340 align:middle line:84%
and realized that
it was an integrated

00:44:03.340 --> 00:44:05.410 align:middle line:90%
approach to how we're living.

00:44:05.410 --> 00:44:08.170 align:middle line:84%
So at the moment,
our current society--

00:44:08.170 --> 00:44:10.450 align:middle line:84%
it's a fragmented
approach to living.

00:44:10.450 --> 00:44:13.640 align:middle line:84%
So everything's
compartmentalized or separated.

00:44:13.640 --> 00:44:15.587 align:middle line:84%
Whereas permaculture
is a holistic approach

00:44:15.587 --> 00:44:16.420 align:middle line:90%
to how we're living.

00:44:16.420 --> 00:44:19.048 align:middle line:90%


00:44:19.048 --> 00:44:23.790 align:middle line:84%
It integrates food, environment
with your lifestyle and taking

00:44:23.790 --> 00:44:28.850 align:middle line:84%
care of people, the planet,
and the natural resources.

00:44:28.850 --> 00:44:31.980 align:middle line:90%


00:44:31.980 --> 00:44:34.400 align:middle line:84%
So a lot of people come
over to our property

00:44:34.400 --> 00:44:36.120 align:middle line:90%
and have a look around.

00:44:36.120 --> 00:44:38.050 align:middle line:84%
And they go, what
about your fruit trees?

00:44:38.050 --> 00:44:39.910 align:middle line:84%
Do you get pests and
stuff like birds?

00:44:39.910 --> 00:44:41.270 align:middle line:90%
And I say, yeah, sure.

00:44:41.270 --> 00:44:42.560 align:middle line:90%
But we don't mind that.

00:44:42.560 --> 00:44:45.050 align:middle line:84%
They were here first, and
we're a part of nature.

00:44:45.050 --> 00:44:49.790 align:middle line:84%
And we've had comments from
other people that live around

00:44:49.790 --> 00:44:51.650 align:middle line:90%
near us on the farms.

00:44:51.650 --> 00:44:54.225 align:middle line:84%
And they say they can't believe
how much wildlife and bird

00:44:54.225 --> 00:44:55.280 align:middle line:90%
life is here.

00:44:55.280 --> 00:45:00.080 align:middle line:84%
And their properties just
a few hundred meters away

00:45:00.080 --> 00:45:03.106 align:middle line:84%
have almost no
wildlife or bird life.

00:45:03.106 --> 00:45:18.190 align:middle line:90%


00:45:18.190 --> 00:45:22.540 align:middle line:84%
So we're attracting
bird life and wildlife

00:45:22.540 --> 00:45:24.478 align:middle line:84%
through just letting
nature be as opposed

00:45:24.478 --> 00:45:25.520 align:middle line:90%
to wanting to control it.

00:45:25.520 --> 00:45:29.590 align:middle line:90%


00:45:29.590 --> 00:45:32.380 align:middle line:84%
Permaculture links
into other aspects

00:45:32.380 --> 00:45:36.610 align:middle line:84%
like collaboration,
localization, food resiliency,

00:45:36.610 --> 00:45:38.440 align:middle line:90%
and networking.

00:45:38.440 --> 00:45:40.420 align:middle line:84%
So it's not just
about growing food.

00:45:40.420 --> 00:45:43.000 align:middle line:84%
It's about connecting
a whole system

00:45:43.000 --> 00:45:47.540 align:middle line:84%
and integrating a whole
system into one's life.

00:45:47.540 --> 00:45:52.070 align:middle line:84%
This lifestyle working on the
land and doing permaculture

00:45:52.070 --> 00:45:55.650 align:middle line:84%
feels more rewarding and like
I'm putting something back.

00:45:55.650 --> 00:45:58.580 align:middle line:84%
We also live a less
consumerist lifestyle,

00:45:58.580 --> 00:46:01.850 align:middle line:90%
so we don't need as much stuff.

00:46:01.850 --> 00:46:03.800 align:middle line:84%
So I haven't got
this constant craving

00:46:03.800 --> 00:46:08.600 align:middle line:84%
for more and more things to
make me feel satisfied or happy.

00:46:08.600 --> 00:46:10.140 align:middle line:90%
So there you have it.

00:46:10.140 --> 00:46:13.310 align:middle line:90%
We have homegrown salad--

00:46:13.310 --> 00:46:15.230 align:middle line:90%
fruit salad and green salad--

00:46:15.230 --> 00:46:16.970 align:middle line:90%
and some eggs.

00:46:16.970 --> 00:46:21.293 align:middle line:84%
And I can't believe
still that I don't

00:46:21.293 --> 00:46:22.460 align:middle line:90%
have to go to a supermarket.

00:46:22.460 --> 00:46:26.090 align:middle line:84%
We've grown all this
ourselves in just three years.

00:46:26.090 --> 00:46:27.690 align:middle line:90%
I'm still amazed.

00:46:27.690 --> 00:46:28.700 align:middle line:90%
So anyone can do it.

00:46:28.700 --> 00:46:37.130 align:middle line:90%


00:46:37.130 --> 00:46:40.430 align:middle line:84%
When I was living
in big cities, it

00:46:40.430 --> 00:46:43.220 align:middle line:84%
was like I had to get away
to connect with nature.

00:46:43.220 --> 00:46:45.800 align:middle line:84%
But when I wake up every
morning, I come outside,

00:46:45.800 --> 00:46:48.770 align:middle line:84%
and I'm immediately
in nature here.

00:46:48.770 --> 00:46:50.360 align:middle line:90%
I don't have that void anymore.

00:46:50.360 --> 00:46:54.375 align:middle line:84%
I've just got this instant
connection and satisfaction.

00:46:54.375 --> 00:46:55.250 align:middle line:90%
It's hard to explain.

00:46:55.250 --> 00:47:01.790 align:middle line:90%


00:47:01.790 --> 00:47:03.670 align:middle line:84%
>> Maybe you've had
this experience,

00:47:03.670 --> 00:47:07.378 align:middle line:84%
feeling like I'm
not living my life.

00:47:07.378 --> 00:47:08.920 align:middle line:84%
I'm living the life
I'm paid to live.

00:47:08.920 --> 00:47:11.560 align:middle line:90%
But what about my life?

00:47:11.560 --> 00:47:16.050 align:middle line:84%
So this is a different
dimension of human nature

00:47:16.050 --> 00:47:22.140 align:middle line:84%
that we need to invoke,
we need to implement.

00:47:22.140 --> 00:47:24.700 align:middle line:84%
We need to create conditions
for that part of human nature

00:47:24.700 --> 00:47:25.500 align:middle line:90%
to blossom.

